          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Natural and isotopically enriched powders were used.",
                " The isotopic compositions were as follows (percent)",
                ".",
                "     Natural Pb                     Pb-204       1.4",
                "                                    Pb-206      24.1",
                "                                    Pb-207      22.1",
                "                                    Pb-208      52.4",
                ".",
                "     Enriched Pb-206                Pb-204       0.01",
                "                                    Pb-206      99.66",
                "                                    Pb-207       0.29",
                "                                    Pb-208       0.05",
                ".",
                "     Enriched Pb-207                Pb-204       0.05",
                "                                    Pb-206       2.36",
                "                                    Pb-207      91.62",
                "                                    Pb-208       6.02",
                ".",
                "     Enriched Pb-208                Pb-204 l.T.  0.01",
                "                                    Pb-206       0.10",
                "                                    Pb-207       0.04",
                "                                    Pb-208      99.86",
                ".",
                " The samples were originally in the form of sulphates,",
                " pbso4, but was converted into oxides, Pb-O. The oxides",
                " were rinsed in water and dried at different tempera-",
                " tures between the measurements to reduce the effects",
                " from the void parts."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHRFL"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Christiansen filters for powder columns of 0.1",
                " cm by 0.1 cm by up to 5 cm. As liquids mixtures of",
                " C2Cl4 and C8H10 were used for scattering densities l",
                " up to 3.0e+10 cm and C6d6 for greater l."
              ]
            }
          ],
